Types of selectors In Css

First is # selectors that is Id selector.

Second is . Selector which is Class Selector.
The CSS class Selector
The class selector selects HTML elements with a specific class attribute.

To select elements with a specific class, write a period (.) character, followed by the class name.

Example
In this example all HTML elements with class="center" will be red and center-aligned: 

.center {
  text-align: center;
  color: red;
}



THE CASCADE 
The order your styles are declared in and linked To
matters

As two tags are selected multiple times then the lastest
is always considered.
lower the line is always considered as latest

which is selected first in conflict:  Inline Style >ID > CLASS > ELEMENT Selector.

!important    is used to tell browser that it most specific then any 
selector. and used to include inside selection 
e.g   button{
    background-color: red !important;
}


Inherit means takes properties from the parent.